cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR

This paper primarily focuses on the cybersecurity domain and preventing poisoning attacks on AI-based threat intelligence systems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of AI systems to extract and analyze data from social media websites, forums, and blogs, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses an ensembled semi-supervised approach to estimate the reputation score of Reddit posts, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the validity of information ingested by AI systems, which can be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
